marc conte the leopold leadership program skip to main content search this site the leopold leadership program about fellows news fellowship information resources login fellowships positions early career environmental scholars new fellowships new positions marc conte marc conte contact information postdoctoral fellow stanford university affiliated with leopold leadership fellow gretchen daily marc conte is a post doctoral fellow at the woods institute for the environment at stanford university his research interests lie within the fields of environmental and public economics focusing on the ability with which environmental policy and voluntary behavior can increase the efficiency of land and resource use decisions and motivate the provision of environmental and other public goods as a contributor to the natural capital project conte has developed and applied ecosystem service valuation models to evaluate the changes in social welfare associated with different policy mechanisms and alternative land use scenarios the blog science upstream provides information on activity at the natural capital project including updates on conte's work conte received a ph d from the bren school of environmental science and management at the university of california santa barbara as a fellow in the nsf funded economics and environmental science igert program he received an ab from dartmouth college in ecology and economics tags 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
